ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Indicate at what time point does the participant complete this questionnaire
Does your husband/head of family give you spending money?
If yes, do you decide how to spend this money?
Husband/other family member took your money when you didn''t want him to.
Husband/other family member took your land/jewelry/poultry/livestock when you didn''t want him to.
Husband/other family member prevented you from visiting your parents
Husband/other family member prevented you from working outside the home.
Freedom from family domination score
Notes: A woman was classified as ''empowered'' and coded as 1 if she said that none of these things had happened to her. The category ''not empowered'' was coded as 0.

ElementDescription: Do you, in your own name, own any land, your homestead land, or your house?
Do you yourself own any productive assets (for example, cattle or sewing machine)?
Do you have any cash savings?
Have you ever used your saving for business or money-landing?
Of your total household expenses what proportion is met through your own earning?
Economic security and contribution score
Notes: A woman with a score of 2 or better was classified as empowered.

ElementDescription: Have you ever been to the bazaar?
Have you ever been to the bazaar alone?
Have you ever been to the hospital/clinic/doctor?
Have you ever been to the hospital/clinic/doctor alone?
Have you ever gone to the cinema?
Have you ever gone to the cinema alone?
Have you ever gone outside the village?
Have you ever gone outside the village alone?
Women''s mobility score
Notes: Each respondent was given 1 point for each place she had visited and an additional point if she had ever gone there alone. The scale ranged from 0 to 8 and was employed as a continuous variable.
